frame.name: Body_parts
frame.definition:
<def-root>This frame covers words for <fen>Body_part</fen>(s) (BP) belonging to a <fen>Possessor</fen> (Poss), which may be characterized by a <fen>Descriptor</fen> (Desc). The location of the BP may be identified in terms of its <fen>Attachment</fen> or its <fen>Orientational_location</fen>. A <fen>Subregion</fen> of a BP may also be indicated. <ex></ex> <ex>He had to brace <fex name="Possessor">his</fex> <fex name="Orientational_location">right</fex> <t><fex name="Body_part">arm</fex></t> against his leg in order to fight the roll.</ex>
<ex>The dog measured <fex name="Possessor">its</fex> <fex name="Descriptor">blond</fex> <t><fex name="Body_part">belly</fex></t> in the mud.</ex>
<ex></ex></def-root>

FE.name: Possessor
FE.definition:
<def-root>This Frame Element denotes the <fen>Possessor</fen> of the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
<ex><fex name="Poss">Kim's</fex> arm is broken.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Descriptor
FE.definition:
<def-root>This Frame Element is used for a characteristic or description of the <fen>Body_part</fen>. Note that <fen>Descriptor</fen> is not an FE of the same character as other FEs. Specifically, rather than filling a slot, it identifies a modifier of its head noun.
<ex>Kim has <fex name="Desc">beautiful</fex> <t>eyes</t>.</ex> <ex>His <fex name="Desc">trembling</fex> <t>hands</t>....</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Body_part
FE.definition: <def-root>This Frame Element is the <fen>Body_part</fen>. <ex>Kim's <fex name="Body_P">arm</fex> is broken.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Subregion
FE.definition:
<def-root>This FEidentifies the <fen>Subregion</fen> of the <fen>Body_part</fen> referred to by the target.
<ex><fex name="Subr">upper</fex> <t>arm</t></ex> <ex><fex name="Subr">lower</fex> <t>back</t></ex></def-root>

FE.name: Orientational_location
FE.definition:
<def-root>This Frame Element describes the location of the <fen>Body_part</fen> with respect to the inherent orientation of the body (or the larger body part) the <fen>Body_part</fen> is attached to.
<ex><fex name="OrLoc">left</fex> <t>leg</t></ex> <ex><fex name="OrLoc">hind</fex> <t>foot</t></ex> <ex><fex name="OrLoc">second</fex> <t>finger</t></ex> <ex><fex name="OrLoc">front</fex> <t>wings</t></ex>
NB: All of these (other than very productive types such as "left", "right", "front", "back", and "second") should be tagged as secondary targets.</def-root>

FE.name: Attachment
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Attachment</fen> is the larger body part to which the BP is attached. <ex>the <t>fingers</t> <fex name="Attachment">of her left hand</fex></ex> <ex>the <t>fin</t> <fex name="Attachment">on its back</fex></ex> <ex>the <fex name="Attachment">dorsal</fex> <t>fin</t></ex></def-root>

lexUnit.name: arm.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: each of the two upper limbs of the human body from the shoulder to the hand.

lexUnit.name: ankle.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the joint connecting the foot with the leg.

lexUnit.name: anus.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the opening at the end of the alimentary canal through which solid waste matter leaves the body.

lexUnit.name: back.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: he rear surface of the human body from the shoulders to the hips.

lexUnit.name: beard.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a growth of hair on the chin and lower cheeks of a man's face.

lexUnit.name: belly.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the front part of the human trunk below the ribs, containing the stomach and bowels.

lexUnit.name: body.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the physical structure, including the bones, flesh, and organs, of a person or an animal.

lexUnit.name: breast.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: either of the two soft, protruding organs on the upper front of a woman's body which secrete milk after pregnancy.

lexUnit.name: buttocks.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the fleshy parts of the human body that form the bottom.

lexUnit.name: cheek.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: either side of the face below the eye, or either of the buttocks.

lexUnit.name: chest.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the front surface of a person's or animal's body between the neck and the stomach.

lexUnit.name: chin.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the protruding part of the face below the mouth, formed by the apex of the lower jaw.

lexUnit.name: ear.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the organ of hearing and balance in humans and other vertebrates, especially the external part of this.

lexUnit.name: earlobe.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a soft, rounded fleshy part hanging from the lower margin of the ear.

lexUnit.name: elbow.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the joint between the forearm and the upper arm.

lexUnit.name: eyelid.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: each of the upper and lower folds of skin which cover the eye when closed.

lexUnit.name: face.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the front part of a person's head from the forehead to the chin, or the corresponding part in an animal.

lexUnit.name: finger.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: each of the four slender jointed parts attached to either hand (or five, if the thumb is included).

lexUnit.name: flesh.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the surface of the human body

lexUnit.name: foot.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the lower extremity of the leg below the ankle, on which a person or animal stands or walks.

lexUnit.name: forearm.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the part of a person's arm extending from the elbow to the wrist or the fingertips.

lexUnit.name: forehead.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the part of the face above the eyebrows.

lexUnit.name: groin.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the area between the abdomen and the thigh on either side of the body, or the region of the genitals.

lexUnit.name: hair.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: any of the fine thread-like strands growing from the skin of mammals and other animals, or from the epidermis of a plant, or such strands collectively, especially those on a person's head.

lexUnit.name: hand.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the end part of the arm beyond the wrist, including the palm, fingers, and thumb.

lexUnit.name: head.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the upper part of the human body, or the front or upper part of the body of an animal, typically separated from the rest of the body by a neck, and containing the brain, mouth, and sense organs.

lexUnit.name: heel.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the back part of the foot below the ankle.

lexUnit.name: incisor.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a narrow-edged tooth at the front of the mouth, adapted for cutting.

lexUnit.name: jaw.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: each of the upper and lower bony structures in vertebrates forming the framework of the mouth and containing the teeth.

lexUnit.name: toe.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: any of the five digits at the end of the human foot

lexUnit.name: hoof.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the horny part of the foot of an ungulate, especially a horse

lexUnit.name: claw.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a curved, pointed horny nail on each digit of the foot in birds, lizards, and some mammals

lexUnit.name: paw.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: an animal's foot having claws and pads

lexUnit.name: talon.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a claw, especially one belonging to a bird of prey

lexUnit.name: wing.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a modified forelimb or other appendage allowing a bird, bat, insect, or other creature to fly.

lexUnit.name: pelt.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the skin of an animal with the fur, wool, or hair still on it.

lexUnit.name: snout.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the projecting nose and mouth of an animal, esp. a mammal

lexUnit.name: maw.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the jaws or throat, esp. of a voracious animal.

lexUnit.name: fang.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: a dangerous tooth, large and sharp and/or capable of delivering poison

lexUnit.name: mane.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a growth of long hair on the neck of a horse, lion, or other animal

lexUnit.name: whisker.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a long projecting hair or bristle growing from the face or snout of an animal such as a cat

lexUnit.name: feeler.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: an animal organ such as an antenna that is used for testing things by touch or for searching for food

lexUnit.name: antler.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a branched horn on the head of an adult deer

lexUnit.name: muzzle.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the projecting part of the face, including the nose and mouth, of an animal such as a dog or horse

lexUnit.name: beak.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a bird's horny projecting jaws; a bill

lexUnit.name: trunk.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the elongated, prehensile nose of an elephant

lexUnit.name: tail.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the hindmost part of an animal, especially when extended beyond the rest of the body, such as the flexible extension of the backbone in a vertebrate or the feathers at the hind end of a bird

lexUnit.name: eye.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the organ of sight in humans or other animals

lexUnit.name: foreleg.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: each of the most anterior limbs used for locomotion or standing.

lexUnit.name: forefoot.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: each of the front feet of a four-footed animal

lexUnit.name: forepaw.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: each of the frontmost paws of an animal

lexUnit.name: limb.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: an arm, leg, or wing

lexUnit.name: fin.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a flattened appendage on the body of a fish or other aquatic animal, used for propelling, steering, and balancing

lexUnit.name: flipper.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a broad, flat limb without fingers, used for swimming by sea animals such as seals, whales, and turtles

lexUnit.name: horn.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a hard permanent outgrowth of bone encased in hardened skin, often curved and pointed, found in pairs on the heads of cattle, sheep, and other animals

lexUnit.name: nape.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the back of a person's neck. NB: not always used of people

lexUnit.name: nose.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the part projecting above the mouth on a person or animal, containing the nostrils and used in breathing and smelling

lexUnit.name: antenna.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a long, thin sensory appendage found in pairs on the heads of insects and some other arthropods.

lexUnit.name: fluke.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: either of the lobes of a whale's tail

lexUnit.name: skin.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a thin layer of tissue forming the natural outer covering of the body of a person or animal

lexUnit.name: forelimb.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: any of the frontmost limbs of a creature

lexUnit.name: hindlimb.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: any of the rearmost limbs of a creature.

lexUnit.name: hindleg.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: any of the hindmost legs of a creature

lexUnit.name: fingertip.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the tip of the finger

lexUnit.name: brow.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a person's forehead

lexUnit.name: lip.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: either of the two fleshy parts forming the edges of the mouth opening.

lexUnit.name: temple.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the flat part either side of the head between the forehead and the ear.

lexUnit.name: fingernail.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the nail on the upper surface of the tip of each finger.

lexUnit.name: tongue.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the fleshy muscular organ in the mouth, used for tasting, licking, swallowing, and (in humans) articulating speech

lexUnit.name: toenail.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a nail on the upper surface of the tip of each toe

lexUnit.name: thumb.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the short, thick first digit of the hand, set lower and apart from the other four and opposable to them.

lexUnit.name: nostril.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: either of two external openings of the nasal cavity in vertebrates that admit air to the lungs and smells to the olfactory nerves.

lexUnit.name: sole.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the underside of a person's foot.

lexUnit.name: midriff.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the region of the front of the body between the chest and the waist

lexUnit.name: navel.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a rounded knotty depression in the center of a person's belly caused by the detachment of the umbilical cord after birth; the umbilicus

lexUnit.name: neck.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the part of a person's or animal's body connecting the head to the rest of the body.

lexUnit.name: hindquarters.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the hind legs and adjoining parts of a quadruped.

lexUnit.name: forefinger.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the finger next to the thumb.

lexUnit.name: thigh.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the part of the leg between the hip and the knee.

lexUnit.name: mouth.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the opening and cavity in the lower part of the face, surrounded by the lips, through which food and air are taken and vocal sounds are emitted

lexUnit.name: tentacle.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a long slender flexible appendage of an animal, used for grasping or moving about, or bearing sense organs.

lexUnit.name: bill.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a. the beak of a bird, especially when it is slender, flattened, or weak, or belongs to a web-footed bird or a bird of the pigeon family

lexUnit.name: appendage.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a projecting part of an organism, with a distinct appearance or function

lexUnit.name: thorax.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the part of the body of any living being between the neck and the abdomen, including the cavity enclosed by the ribs, breastbone, and dorsal vertebrae.

lexUnit.name: rump.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: .the hind part of the body of a mammal, the lower back of a bird, or humourously a person's buttocks

lexUnit.name: crown.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the top part of a person's head.

lexUnit.name: member.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a man's penis

lexUnit.name: leg.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: each of the limbs on which a person or animal walks and stands.

lexUnit.name: shoulder.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: the joint between the upper arm or forelimb and the main part of the body.

lexUnit.name: tooth.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: a hard structure in the mouth of some animals often used for chewing and other purposes

lexUnit.name: mustache.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: thick hair between the upper lip and the nose extending often to the corners of the mouth.

lexUnit.name: knee.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: a joint between the upper and lower leg that projects forward and is protected by the patella.

lexUnit.name: pupil.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the dark circular center of the eye surrounded by the iris

lexUnit.name: throat.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the portion of the body that is positioned between the chin and the top of the shoulders

lexUnit.name: lung.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: the internal organs for breathing
